The paper discusses performance metrics for high-throughput optical communication systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of soft decision forward error correction (SD-FEC) and bit interleaving suggests a focus on error correction and coding theory (cs.DS). The study of prediction accuracy for post-FEC bit error rate may also involve networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
